HEADWORD: Pleximeter
<hw>Plex*im"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ stroke,
percussion (from <?/ to strike) + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A small, hard, elastic plate, as of ivory, bone,
or rubber, placed in contact with body to receive the blow, in
examination by mediate percussion.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>plexometer</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plexure</ent>⟦br⟧
